HEADWORD: Cutlass
<hw>Cut"lass</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧t"l⟦ait⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Cutlasses</plw> <pr>(-⟦ecr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[F. <ets>coutelas</ets> (cf. It. <ets>coltellaccio</ets>), augm.
fr. L. <ets>cuttellus</ets> a small knife, dim. of <ets>culter</ets>
knife. See <er>Colter</er>, and cf. <er>Curtal ax</er>.]</ety> <def>A
short, heavy, curving sword, used in the navy. See <er>Curtal
ax</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
